Sentencas: The porous cermet of Yb-doped BaZrO3 and nickel (BZYb-Ni) for anode-supported protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFCs) was fabricated by compression molding following the liquid condensation process (LCP).
Titulo: Pore structure improvement in cermet for anode-supported protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The gas permeability of BZYb-Ni produced by LCP (BZYb-Ni-LCP) was greater than that of BZYb-Ni produced by a conventional drying method (BZYb-Ni-CDM) although their porosities were similar.
Titulo: Pore structure improvement in cermet for anode-supported protonic ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The greater permeability of BZYb-Ni-LCP than that of BZYb-Ni-CDM is consistent with more efficient structures for gas flow; a smaller specific surface area, and a larger critical diameter for pores in BZYb-Ni-LCP than those for pores in BZYb-Ni-CDM.
Titulo: Pore structure improvement in cermet for anode-supported protonic ceramic fuel cells
